history.text: Hi, what's up?
Hi,
Have you ever seen Batman Begins? A lot of people didn't like Bale as Batman, but I thought he was really good.
Yes. I have seen batman.
Wasn't it a great movie? I think honestly that was the best of the trilogy. Even though we've seen how he became Batman before, it was still a great movie.
Plus it had Liam Neeson acting menacing, and he's really good at that. Katie Holmes I could have done without.
Yes. But I only see the first one.
Well, you saw the right one. lol
12 years ago?
Yeah 13, now. It came out in 2005. That's hard to believe. Seems more recent.
I cannot remember the plot. Only remember a little.
It starts with him as a kid, explores how he was afraid of bats, and then shows his parent's murder.
It really focused more on how Bruce could be a real person driven to be a superhero.
Ok.
Are we going to talk about only this one?
As far as I know yes, unless you have a movie you want to discuss.
Ok.  The movie is nice. It is thrilling.
It was, and Bale really pulled off playing both Wayne and Batman as two distinct personalities and was believable as both.
Yes. still remember that he put on the batman outfit and jumped.
You really feel his frustration against the corruption of Gotham when he wants to take out Joe Chill after the trial, but Falcone's men take him out instead.
I did not remember, but you can tell more.

It was at the beginning, he wants to kill his parent's murderer, but the crime boss' men take him out first. Then he leaves Gotham to go train with Liam Neeson and the League of Shadows off in Tibet or wheerever.
Then he learns they want to destroy Gotham because it's too far gone and he burns down the place, but saves Neeson as Ra's al Ghul dies in the fire.
Ok. Need to see the movie again.
Haha, there's a lot of details you can miss.
Ok.
It's after that he comes back to Gotham and becomes Batman.
Where Scarecrow first surfaces and uses his fear gas on him
Then you find out the League of Shadows was using Scarecrow to gas Gotham into oblivion and watch the city tear itself apart.
Ok.
And that Liam Neeson was really Ra's Al Ghul, not the guy you see in the training building.
It is a nice movie.
It is, pretty high-rated across the board.
Try to see it once more time.
Do you own the movie?
No.
I have the entire series. Watched them with my kids last year.
Good.
They didn't give you any movies to discuss as well?
No.

uid1response.feedback: Other user seemed confused and disinterested.
